equired to move forward with restoring production has been reached said donald currie hillcrest chief executive being approved as operator in the province of alberta was required for hillcrest too coordinate work programs with local service companies and vendors the company will update the shareholders as we progress towards production of the assets hillcrest said total project financing including the placement of operator deposits and licence liability rating llr bonds is estimated to cost mln and will be secured from a third party by both the assets and the company it is estimated that around c will be needed to bring production back on line via equipment installation and upgrades and well workovers these projects are expected to reduce operating expenses and restore production thereby increasing the operating netbacks project costs include the placement of around mln llr bonds the company expects to recover these bonds once economic production from the fields has been reestablished for a period thereby substantially reducing the net investment in the project shares in toronto are down over  on thursday at  top stories former twitter executive adam bain tipped to become next pandora media ceo iphone th anniversary looking back at apples first handset and what to expect for iphone  voltaic minerals gearing up for lowcost lithium exploration in utah’s paradox basin view full hrh profile view profile hillcrest petroleum ltd timeline article july   hillcrest petroleum completes fundraising round newswire june   hillcrest petroleum putting finishing touches to private placement newswire may   hillcrest petroleum books profit after restructuring video may   hillcrest petroleums don currie on western canada acquisition article may   hillcrest petroleum goes for it in western canada big picture february   hillcrest to earn  of western canadian petroleum assets newswire january   hillcrest petroleum raises a further c in oversubscribed placing newswire december   hillcrest